    <item>
      <title>Challenge for Honor</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=paladinbalance&amp;message.id=26989#M26989</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I know I was excited about this spell when it came out, but I have to say, that excitement has...dwindled over time...(there's a bad pun in there).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I just want to share with other Paladins my write up for this spell on my own guild forums, and maybe draw some attention to the things that need fixing on it&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;"I gave Challenge of Honour a test raid spell set spell and it just doesn't work.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Reasons being 1) it has no hardcoded initial aggro even if resisted. 2) the spell is 0.5 seconds extra to cast, which in the tank caster realm can be an eternity in crucial moments. 3) 10% extra mitigation for a total of 500hp is about as useful as a chocolate fireguard. 4) A lot of Knight offtanking is very short and you need the guarranteed spam aggro of Akera (1300) on that 3rd stun. 5) At RK3, you still need over 12 seconds of Challenge to come close to the aggro you gained on Akera. Incidentaly the recast time on Akera is 12 seconds for 1300 *guarranteed*, faster casting aggro. 6) Ok I pulled a mob while grouping with this spell, Flossy (cleric&amp;nbsp;friend)&amp;nbsp;did nothing and I ran behind her and the mob trained on to her. This tells me maybe the spell only even aggros on the next tick.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Add to all that I was rubbish on Sendaii (using challenge) the other day and on top form on CoA/Vish (using akera)&amp;nbsp;last night.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The only raid application I can see for Challenge, is that with my boots, I can get maybe an extra 2 ticks out of it, so I can taunt a mezzed mob on Sendaii, cast one spell and get maybe 722x7 aggro for the cast of one spell.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In grouping i love the spell. I pop Ward of Tunare, Challenge one mob for pull, stun another, Xaz (my BL friend!) offtanks the 3rd. Challenge generally always does enough aggro to counter heal aggro. And if i feel DPS is high, first heal I give myself burst of sunlight, which seems great aggro."&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 21 Nov 2006 13:00:33 GMT</pubDate>
